\cs15\fs16\insrsid4924940 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4924940 Noble savage}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637404 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4924940 `}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637404 
\par She was thought to be about fifty years of age at the time she was found. As near as could be made out by her signs she had, at the time of being left on the island, two children, one of which was a nursing babe, the other some years older, though in the 
opinion of some the elder child had died some years previously. She had a smooth face, though the skin on her body was much winkled [wrinkled]. It was but a short time before her death that they succeeded in making her understand their desire to have some
 words of her own language. The following are about all that were learned of it: A hide she called "tocah"; man, "nache"; the sky, "toy-gwah"; the body, "puoo-chay".
\par 
\par {\*\atrfstart 416435513}She was like a child in every respect as to her appetite, having no control whatever. She was exclusively fond of fruit, which she would eat at all hazards. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid4924940 
{\*\atrfend 416435513}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 416435513}{\*\atndate 1730671329}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid4924940 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4924940 Noble savage}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637404 It produced a dysentary [dysentery], which in spite of careful nursing and attendance, terminated fatally in about four weeks. During her sickness it
 was thought that a diet of seal's meat, such as she had been accustomed to, would relieve her. {\*\atrfstart 416435514}
Some was procured and roasted, but she shook her head and laughed, and rubbed her fingers along her worn-out teeth, signifying that they were too old.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid4924940 {\*\atrfend 416435514}{\*\atnid SS}
{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 416435514}{\*\atndate 1730671329}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 
\ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid4924940 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4924940 Signs easily interpreted}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637404  She was buried by the Mission fathers and most of her island trinkets and her shag feather dresses were sent to Rome and found in a place in the Vatican museum.
\par 
\par {\*\atrfstart 416435515}In conclusion, we can but question ourselves. What kept this lone woman's heart warm through all her long years of solitude, with no companions but those wild Russian dogs? {\*\atrfstart 416435516}
When found at last she was as blythe and sunny as a child, with a heart still as warm as that of any child, with love and gratitude for her deliverance at last, and again, why that other, her best dress? Why was it? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs15\fs16\insrsid11743687 {\*\atrfend 416435516}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 416435516}{\*\atndate 120143227}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
